# Enter your code here!
m <- mean(mtcars$mpg)
v <- var(mtcars$mpg)
s <- sd(mtcars$mpg)



print(paste("The average of Mile Per Gallon from this data set is", m  , "with variance",v, " and standard deviation", s , "."))

  1. Create a crosstab that shows the number of observations belong to each cylinder and gear class combinations. The table should show how many observations given the car has 4 cylinders with 3 gears, 4 cylinders with 4 gears, etc. Report which combination is recorded in this data set and how many observations for this type of car.
# Enter your code here!

crosstab <- table(mtcars$cyl, mtcars$gear)
print(crosstab)
##    
##      3  4  5
##   4  1  8  2
##   6  2  4  1
##   8 12  0  2
most_common_combination <- which.max(crosstab)
cyl_gear_combination <- dimnames(crosstab)[[1]][most_common_combination]
gear_gear_combination <- dimnames(crosstab)[[2]][most_common_combination]
num_cars <- crosstab[most_common_combination]

print(paste("The most common car type in this data set is car with", cyl_gear_combination, "cylinders and", gear_gear_combination, "gears. There are a total of", num_cars, "cars belonging to this specification in the data set."))
## [1] "The most common car type in this data set is car with 8 cylinders and 5 gears. There are a total of 12 cars belonging to this specification in the data set."
